<TEXT>
more than 2500 police called for the 
ouster of gov jim florio and attorney general robert del tufo 
during a rally wednesday supporting a white police officer who 
fatally shot a black teenager 
organizers said police are angry because the state has empaneled 
a second grand jury to investigate the april 10 shooting of 
16yearold phillip c pannell by teaneck officer gary spath 
were here to send them our message which is they have to 
stop using officer spath and partner wayne blanco as pawns in 
their political game said steve librie president of the teaneck 
policemens benevolent association theyre trying to make spath 
a scapegoat for everything thats wrong with society 
the officers rallied outside the bergen county courthouse in 
hackensack chanting dump del tufo dump florio they then 
marched several miles from hackensack to teaneck and congregated 
outside a municipal building 
meanwhile about 40 people gathered outside a teaneck school for 
a prayer vigil in memory of pannell 
those 2000 officers are walking strong with their guns 
said donna jackson a newark coordinator for the united youth 
council a black organization that has supported the pannell family 
we sit back and say its not affecting me or my family you 
think that youre wrong next time it could be you jackson said 
after the shooting police and witnesses offered sharply 
different accounts of the moments leading up to the incident 
spath and blanco who were responding to a complaint of a youth 
with a gun have said spath fired only when he saw pannell reaching 
for a gun at his waist witnesses said pannell had his hands in the 
air when the shot was fired 
a second grand jury is to review the evidence because of a 
faulty autopsy report to the first grand jury by bergen county 
medical examiner lawrence denson del tufo said medical evidence 
indicates that pannells hands were in the air 
the rallying police officers black and white chanted he 
had a gun 
nutley police officer steven rogers said more than 2500 
officers attended the rally 
</TEXT>
