<TEXT>
bernard wex designer of the worlds longest 
suspension bridge span has died according to a newspaper report 
today he was 68 
the london newspaper the independent reported that wex died on 
july 31 it stated no cause of death and gave no explanation for 
threeweek delay in reporting it 
wex designed the humber estuary bridge in northeast england 
which was officially opened by queen elizabeth ii in 1981 
the guinness book of records lists its main span measuring 
4626 feet as the worlds longest suspension bridge span 
as partnerincharge with the firm of consulting engineers 
freeman fox and partners wex both designed the bridge and directed 
its construction 
wex graduated with honors in civil engineering from londons 
prestigious imperial college in 1951 and then joined freeman fox 
working under the internationally renowned bridge designer gilbert 
roberts 
wex was involved in the design of several important bridges 
under the guidance of roberts and later oleg kerensky they 
included the auckland harbor bridge in new zealand and the severn 
and forth road suspension bridges both in britain 
he was honored by the queen for his services to engineering by 
being made an officer of the order of the british empire in 1982 
he leaves a wife and two sons the report did not mention 
funeral services 
</TEXT>
