defense secretary dick cheney and gen colin powell chairman of 
the joint chiefs of staff planned to tell bush today that the 
united states was approaching a target figure of 100000 military 
personnel in the region 
the transportation strain has fallen most heavily on the 
pentagons airlift operation johnson said because of the need in 
the earliest stage of desert shield to get as many light infantry 
on the ground in saudi arabia as possible 
he described the air operation as the largest sustained 
airlift ever over a short period of time 
besides the workhorse c141 and c5 military transport planes 
used to ferry men and equipment johnson said the pentagon has 
relied heavily on the commercial airline industry several airlines 
volunteered to provide charter passenger service he said but late 
last week the pentagon decided to commandeer 38 civilian cargo and 
passenger jets because the volunteer pool was too small 
johnson said he didnt expect to force additional commercial 
planes into service 
