sri lanka the government has said it will not stop trade with 
iraq sanctions can be imposed by rich countries we cannot 
afford to stop selling our products says deputy defense minister 
ranjan wijeratne 
sri lanka sells tea worth 100 million to iraq every year and 
receives about 500000 from its citizens working in the gulf 
according to government figures gasoline and cooking prices have 
been raised 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
yugoslavia construction companies were involved in projects 
worth 1 billion in iraq also baghdad owes yugoslavia 11 
billion and was repaying with supplies of crude oil 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
zambia zambia has announced a 50 percent increase in fuel and 
kerosene because of the gulf crisis 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
