<TEXT>
nasa says it has ruled out the possibility 
that household washers in a measuring device caused the hubble 
space telescopes focusing flaw 
just when we thought we knew were back to square one said 
charles pellerin nasa director of astrophysics its 
frustrating 
nasa investigators had suggested last week that improperly 
installed washers 13 millimeters thick might have caused the 
13millimeter flaw in the mirror which is producing blurred 
images from the orbiting telescope 
but pellerin said tuesday the investigators had only estimated 
the thickness of the washers last week when the washers were 
measured they turned out to be much thinner too thin to have 
caused the mirror flaw he said 
now he said its increasingly possible that the cause of the 
mirror flaw was a mathematical error made in transposing the design 
of the measuring device known as a reflective null corrector from 
the drawing board to the assembly room 
the 15 billion telescope was supposed to provide unprecedented 
views of outer space its 94inch primary mirror was made from 1979 
to 1982 by the perkinelmer corp whose optical division in 
danbury was bought last year by hughes danbury optical systems 
the nasa team visited hughes twice to review data and test 
results 
last thursday the investigators said there was an estimated 13 
millimeter error between the mirror and the field lens of the 
reflective null corrector which guides the grinding and polishing 
of a mirror 
the boards strongest hypothesis was that three washers had 
mistakenly been inserted into a plate that held a lens in place in 
the null corrector they werent certain though that the washers 
were to blame at all 
charles spoelhof a member of the investigative team said the 
board only estimated the washers thickness because they were still 
mounted inside the reflective null corrector and werent accessible 
when the washers were measured a few days ago at hughes they 
were found to be just 75 millimeters thick by precision optical 
standards a huge spacing difference from the estimated 
13millimeter thickness pellerin said 
