<TEXT>
the five permanent members of the un 
security council met today to try to draft a resolution calling for 
a military blockade to enforce international economic sanctions 
against iraq 
the soviet union has slowed us efforts to get un approval 
for a military blockade western diplomats say and the private 
meeting today was expected to discuss soviet concerns 
the diplomats said tuesday that moscow has sought clear and 
demonstrable failure of the un embargo before approving any un 
military force 
china had dragged its feet for the same reason but a kuwaiti 
official in beijing said today the chinese government promised not 
to block such a move 
the meeting was held at the french mission and involved 
representatives from the united states soviet union china 
britain and france 
on his way into the meeting us ambassador thomas r pickering 
said well be continuing our consultations in the day pushing 
toward hopefully trying to do something today if its at all 
possible 
asked if the soviets were blocking progress pickering replied 
well i dont put my finger on anybody well wait and see 
soviet foreign minister eduard a shevardnadze said in an 
interview published tuesday that some elements of iraqi president 
saddam husseins proposal to end the middle east crisis merit 
serious attention 
saddam offered on sunday to free thousands of foreign hostages 
in iraq and iraqioccupied kuwait if the usled multinational 
force protecting saudi arabia from iraqi aggression withdraws and 
the united states guarantees the un embargo on iraq will be 
lifted 
i think that there are elements which attract attention 
shevardnadze was quoted as telling the soviet newspaper pravda 
we are studying all the details all the blocks of the speech of 
the president of iraq 
the western diplomats speaking on condition of anonymity said 
the soviet and chinese objections have slowed the momentum for 
tougher measures following the nearunanimity of the security 
council in four previous votes against iraqs invasion of kuwait on 
aug 2 
the permanent security council members deliberated a 
precedentsetting proposal tuesday that would authorize foreign 
naval vessels to use minimum force in policing the un embargo no 
final action was taken any of the five permanent council members 
can kill council resolutions with a veto 
the soviets in the past week have wanted to revive the military 
staff committee before imposing a blockade the committee consists 
of military officers of the five permanent officers to coordinate 
un enforcement actions but it has never had an active role even 
during the 195053 korean war 
soviet ambassador valentin lozinsky last week told security 
council that the soviets would participate in a blockade only under 
a un flag 
for the second day in a row shevardnadze met in moscow tuesday 
with iraqi deputy prime minister saadoun hammadi but the soviet 
news agency tass gave few details of their talks hammadi also 
spoke with soviet prime minister nikolai ryzhkov who urged iraq to 
allow foreigners to leave its territory 
 
kuwaits foreign minister sheik sabah alahmed said in beijing 
today that china has promised not to veto military enforcement of 
the un embargo he met this morning with premier li peng and 
foreign minister wu xueqian but the kuwaiti official did not say 
from whom he extracted the promise 
chinese ambassador li daoyu in the first public statement about 
the beijing governments stand said tuesday that security council 
decisions thus far imply no permission for military involvement 
by big powers and their naval blockade 
under the present circumstances he told the xinhua news 
agency resort to military actions will lead to further 
aggravation of the situation and escalation of the armed conflict 
which does not help solving the problem 
he urged that efforts be channeled through the security 
councils sanctions committee before military action was authorized 
li did not say how china would vote on military involvement but 
diplomats said china was likely to abstain and not cast a lone 
veto all five permanent council members have veto power and can 
kill any resolution 
the united states britain and france were supportive of a 
unique resolution which would provide a un umbrella but not a 
un flag and command for international warships enforcing the 
embargo britains un ambassador argued that such a possible 
momentous step requires that all nations move extremely 
carefully 
in a display of unprecedented cooperation the 15member 
security council has adopted four mandatory resolutions in the past 
three weeks condemning iraqs aug 2 invasion of kuwait calling 
for sweeping economic sanctions against iraq rejecting iraqs 
annexation of kuwait and demanding freedom for thousands of 
foreigners held against their will in iraq and kuwait 
under article 42 of the un charter the security council may 
call for a blockade and enforcement of its embargo through military 
force if its earlier sanctions have been violated article 42 
never has been invoked for a un enforcement action 
