<TEXT>
military experts sent to iraq before its invasion 
of kuwait continue working for the iraqi government despite a 
kremlin order to sever all trade and financial ties with baghdad a 
soviet colonel said today 
the 193 soviet experts have been training iraqi soldiers to use 
sovietbuilt weapons repairing and maintaining those weapons and 
building test ranges col valentin ogurtsov told a news briefing 
they are fulfilling their contractual duties he said 
soviet experts are not involved in military operations and did 
not provide advice for iraqs aug 2 invasion of kuwait he said 
soviet prime minister nikolai ryzhkov issued an order to all 
soviet agencies earlier today to cut business ties with iraq to 
comply with un sanctions the tass news agency reported 
the soviet union had been iraqs main arms supplier providing 
most of its modern tanks missiles and jet fighters 
but the day after the iraqi invasion the soviet union cut arms 
supplies to baghdad and ogurtsov said one weapons shipment was 
stopped in transit foreign minister eduard shevardnadze and us 
secretary of state james a baker iii signed a joint statement 
condemning iraqs attack on its oilrich neighbor 
but the soviet union together with china has slowed us 
efforts at the united nations for military action to back up the 
economic embargo of iraq western diplomats say 
foreign ministry spokesman yuri gremitskikh rejected repeated 
questions about whether the continuing work by the military experts 
violated the un emgargo and the soviet government order 
he said nationals from other countries continued to work in 
iraq although he did not identify the nations or jobs their 
nationals were performing 
iraq has made hostages out of thousands of foreigners who were 
trapped in iraq and kuwait by the invasion iraq has also moved 
some foreigners to iraqi military installations to prevent an 
attack by a usled multinational force being deployed in saudi 
arabia to protect it against iraqi aggression 
this is not a simple solution gremitskikh said dont 
single out the soviet union i dont think this presence runs 
counter to the united nations position 
ogurtsov said that when the soviet government contracted to sell 
weapons to iraq it also agreed to provide technical experts to 
show iraq how to use them 
gremitskikh said when the contracts expire the experts will 
leave and will not be replaced the contracts range from 10 days to 
one year ogurtsov said 
at the present time they work not only in training centers 
but on test ranges suppose we supplied a new type of tank it has 
new unknown capabilities to the local personnel so we build a kind 
of test range to test it this is the kind of activity they are 
involved in ogurtsov said 
we are trying to make the period of stay shorter and shorter 
but we are going to phase out the work eventually ogurtsov said 
the military experts were among 7791 soviets stranded in iraq 
after its attack on kuwait gremitskikh said soviet women and 
children would begin to be evacuated from iraq on sunday he 
indicated that iraq would then allow soviet men to be evacuated 
also today a special envoy from saudi arabia arrived in moscow 
the soviet union has no diplomatic relations with the kingdom 
gremitskikh said iraqs deputy prime minister saadoun hammadi met 
with shevardnadze monday and tuesday 
saudi arabia and moscow had full diplomatic relations until 
1938 when dictator josef stalin closed his embassy in jiddah to 
cut costs 
several attempts to reestablish ties during the 1980s faltered 
over what saudia arabia called the soviet unions belligerent 
attitude toward its 50 million moslems 
