the citys new police chief has two unresolved 
departmental charges against him according to a georgia bureau of 
investigation report 
atlanta police department records on eldrin a bell show the 
departments internal affairs unit recommended charges against him 
in 1989 for allegedly operating a security business in the city a 
conflict of interest and doing it without departmental permission 
the records were contained in the gbi report given to mayor 
maynard jackson prior to bells nomination for police chief which 
the atlanta city council approved monday 
bell refused to speak with reporters tuesday and denied there 
were open charges against him he also has maintained he no longer 
has an interest in a security business 
the mayor who said monday the gbi report contained nothing new 
first said tuesday there were no open charges but later criticized 
former chief morris g redding for not resolving the open charges 
before retiring last month 
the first time i found out the former chief did not do his 
duty was over the past few days said jackson who has asked 
acting city attorney joe harris to look into the matter 
the charges allege bell who will oversee a force of 1590 
officers operated a security business based in the zone he 
commanded in 1988 and that he hired offduty zone officers to work 
for his firm taking care of business inc 
the allegations against bell were made by the international 
brotherhood of police officers union 
deputy chief wj taylor who was acting chief and a finalist 
for the job said he was aware of the unresolved charges against 
bell but did not act 
i thought it inappropriate to adjudicate disciplinary action 
against another candidate he said 
he said the file was still sitting on the desk where redding 
left it when he retired i didnt read the file he said 
i had decided not to make a decision until the new chief is 
appointed i wanted to remain neutral redding said in a july gbi 
interview 
he added that if the charges were upheld bell could have faced 
a maximum one or twoday suspension 
