in new york declined to specifically blame the soviets for 
footdragging but said he hoped for action on the matter today 
western nations today renewed angry protests over the roundup of 
foreigners trapped in the wake of the invasion denmark warned iraq 
could be trying to split the west by selective hostageholding 
in washington the state department today announced the us 
intention to defy saddams demand to close the us embassy in 
kuwait by friday but said it would reduce the staff other 
nations including britain have announced plans to do the same 
state department spokesman richard boucher said the decision was 
consistent with our obligations to the american private 
community of about 2500 people in kuwait an estimated 500 
americans are trapped in iraq 
pope john paul ii in his first public comment on the crisis 
today pointed to the the danger of war and offered a prayer for 
peace a day earlier the pontiff met with the vatican envoy to 
both iraq and kuwait to discuss the situation and papal spokesman 
joaquin navarro said the diplomat is ready to pursue any 
humanitarian initiatives if asked 
meanwhile an iraqi tanker that had defied warning shots from an 
american warship reached yemens port of aden today and dropped 
anchor near two other iraqi ships already docked there yemen had 
told the un security council that it would adhere to the 
sanctions against iraq 
yemeni officials would not comment on the tankers presence 
today but the official yemeni news agency quoted an unidentified 
foreign ministry official on tuesday as saying yemen did not intend 
to intercept or obstruct any ships 
with no sign of letup in the crisis the tokyo stock market 
tumbled today oil prices edged higher in london on crisis jitters 
today and were also up in latemorning trade on the new york 
mercantile exchange 
in diplomatic activity on the crisis saudi prince bandar bin 
sultan arrived in the soviet union the official soviet news agency 
tass said also egyptian president hosni mubarak conferred today 
with japanese foreign minister taro nakayama on the gulf crisis 
egypts middle east news agency said 
also today defense ministers from the sixnation gulf 
