but under grilling from schiff miller appeared to contradict 
the defenses contention of undue religious influence 
when you made those statements that you gave documents to a 
soviet spy those admissions had nothing to do with religion did 
they schiff asked 
after a long pause miller answered no 
us district judge robert takasugi refused to suppress the 
admission on tuesday saying he would take into account the 
question of religious influence when he weighs the admission as 
evidence takasugi is hearing the case without a jury 
in two earlier trials miller a 20year veteran of the agency 
was portrayed as a fat bumbler who had an affair with a married 
soviet emigre 
prosecutors said miller now a private investigators assistant 
became bitter and vengeful after repeated fbi reprimands over his 
ballooning weight and inept performance 
