italian cardinal luigi dadaglio who held 
several vatican diplomatic posts in north and south america died 
wednesday at the age of 75 
the vatican said dadaglio had been hospitalized at romes 
policlinico gemelli hospital for several days with a heart ailment 
born in northern italys piedmont region dadaglio was ordained 
a priest in 1937 and joined the vatican secretariat of state five 
years later 
he went on to serve in vatican diplomatic missions in haiti 
dominican republic the united states canada australia colombia 
venezuela and spain in the united states he served in washington 
from 195053 
while dadaglio was posted in madrid the vatican and the spanish 
government signed five accords in 1979 regulating churchstate 
relations 
elevated to cardinal by pope john paul ii in 1985 he helped 
organize activities marking the churchs marian year in 198788 
in a message of condolence the pope praised dadaglio for his 
long and generous service in multiple posts carried out with 
competence and dedication on behalf of the church and the holy 
see 
dadaglios death brings the number of members of the college of 
cardinals to 145 of those 109 are under the age of 80 and thus 
eligible to take part in a conclave to elect a new pope 
