either of palestinian origin or from the israelioccupied west bank 
and gaza strip 
in part because of popular sentiment in favor of iraq king 
hussein has still not committed himself fully to upholding un 
sanctions against iraq 
another consideration is that jordan depends heavily on trade 
with its neighbor through the red sea port at aqaba sanctions 
would add to the kingdoms economic woes 
asked whether he was siding with his close ally iraq or with 
the united states in the conflict he said my country is not 
siding with anyone but itself and with the arab people and its 
hopes and aspirations 
any escalation of the conflict would have a devastating effect 
on this region and the world he said 
the king added that he did not believe iraq planned further 
expansion 
i believe that as far as you can tell iraq is holding a fully 
defensive posture and i have the impression that the arab forces 
arrayed against iraq in the area are in a defensive posture 
hussein said 
hussein said his country was seeking to clarify with the united 
nations what trade with iraq is barred by the un resolution 
ordering sanctions against iraq 
there is an area of ambiguity that we have been trying to 
