<TEXT>
donnita cole knows how to wait 
she has acquired the art of patience through three decades of 
fearing for her husband an overseas oil worker familiar with 
quamires like the one that has trapped him in the middle east 
since the 1960s john cole of odessa texas has endured a coup 
in libya an attempted coup in indonesia two nigerian revolutions 
and one in iran 
now the 50yearold employee of houstonbased oge drilling co 
is among about 3000 us citizens detained three weeks after 
iraqs saddam hussein invaded kuwait on aug 2 
the persian gulf crisis is for the cole family yet another in a 
string of crises 
hes not an adventurer hes just trying to make the best 
living he knows how to for me and the kids mrs cole 48 said 
in a telephone interview wednesday from odessa 
and theres more while mrs cole is wearing a yellow ribbon for 
her missing husband she is also flying an american flag in front 
of her home as a reminder of family members on military standby 
her 22yearold twin sons both army combat specialists and a 
soninlaw with the air force are waiting to find out whether 
theyll be sent to the gulf one of the sons whose names mrs cole 
wont reveal was sent with the us troops to panama in december 
weve never really thought about it but we have not led a 
dull life mrs cole said but as far as going out and looking 
for excitement we havent its just that its happened to us 
during the iranian revolution cole escaped from an offshore rig 
by boat and ended up in bahrain mrs cole who was living in 
malta spent nine days without word from her husband listening to 
tales of atrocities from fleeing refugees 
that decadeold experience helped prepare her for this one she 
said 
it hasnt made it easier but its helping me handle it 
better it is never easy to handle anything like this she said 
you learn how to wait and i am not a patient person not at 
all 
mrs cole was planning to join her husband in kuwait aug 15 
instead she is waiting for news from her husband a network of 
families with relatives either deployed or held in the middle east 
are helping her sort through fears both as a hostages wife and as 
a military mother 
i think two different sets of thoughts sometimes they fit 
together and sometimes they dont she said 
