jordan closed its border with iraq at 
midnight wednesday as the country found itself unable to handle the 
flood of tens of thousands of refugees fleeing iraq and kuwait 
the announcement of the border closure came just hours after 
king hussein told a nationally televised news conference that 
42000 foreigners had entered jordan on wednesday the largest 
number of arrivals in a single day since the aug 2 iraqi invasion 
of kuwait 
interior minister salem masdeh said jordans northeast border 
with iraq would close at midnight wednesday 5 pm edt 
msadeh said the border was being closed because of concern for 
the health situation of the arrivals and to ensure suitable 
arrangements for their stay in jordan 
until we provide them with suitable shelter we find ourselves 
obliged to close the jordanian border for the foreign arrivals from 
iraq as of midnight wednesday he said 
