of 30000 foreigners who entered jordan on friday a jordanian 
security official said most of the refugees had arrived in the last 
10 days 
hussein said about 185000 refugees have crossed into jordan 
since aug 2 and only 67000 of them have moved on to other 
destinations the overwhelming majority of arrivals have been arab 
and asian nationals about 40 percent of them egyptians 
of the nearly 120000 refugees who remain in jordan he said 
we are finding enormous difficulty in meeting the needs of these 
people or in arranging adequate modes of transport for them to 
leave jordan 
