troubleplagued nasa restored steady 
radio contact with magellan on wednesday after losing touch with 
the malfunctioning spacecraft for the second time since it started 
orbiting venus 
engineers received radio signals from magellan at about 433 
pm pdt showing that its secondary antenna obeyed computer orders 
and was firmly pointed at earth allowing them to maintain a 
continuous link with the wayward spaceship said tommy thompson 
magellan science manager at nasas jet propulsion laboratory 
it took a ton off our shoulders he said were going home 
with smiles on our faces 
intermittent contact had been restored at 1232 pm pdt when a 
brief blip of a radio signal was received by nasas deep space 
network tracking station in goldstone calif that was about 17 
hours after contact was lost tuesday night laboratory spokesman 
bob macmillin said 
