to yugoslav media and politicians the internal conflict is the 
culmination of a power struggle building since the death in 1980 of 
josip tito who founded communist yugoslavia and ruled it for 35 
years 
how it comes out will determine whether the six divergent 
republics stick together or yugoslavia becomes the first country in 
postwar europe to split up 
for mladen kresic the serb and his two friends tension is 
more personal who spits at whom and which old acquaintances turn 
their backs 
at this point its a confrontation between individuals its 
not a confrontation between two groups he said speaking of 
serbs and croats 
