croatian village in a serbdominated area of croatia 
anything could happen he said and sighed 
serbs and croats are the two largest ethnic groups in 
yugoslavia relations between them have grown worse since croatia 
the secondlargest republic held free elections in april 
elections in three other republics this fall are expected to 
exacerbate ethnic tensions and political divisions 
the centerright croatian democratic union won croatias 
elections the communist leaders of serbia yugoslavias largest 
republic accuse the party of being too nationalistic 
abiding divisions lend heat to the debate 
croats ruled by the hapsburgs for centuries are roman catholic 
and write in latin script serbs dominated by ottoman turks for 
more than 500 years are orthodox and use cyrillic script 
