carolina to work in waterburys brass factories his mother is a 
lifelong republican and he speaks often of his family when he 
explains how he came to his views on selfsufficiency 
my father came here about 55 years ago from north carolina 
franks said he had a sixthgrade education barely could read 
barely could write and my parents raised six children i have 
three sisters who hold doctorate degrees today 
the last black republican in the house was oscar de priest of 
chicago who was elected in the hoover landslide of 1928 and served 
three terms 
the predominantly working class district franks hopes to 
represent is only 4 percent black and he is up against a 
wellknown democrat former congressman and tv anchor toby moffett 
but no one is discounting the threeterm alderman who has won 
respect from democrats and republicans alike during his tenure 
of the three black republicans running for congress this year 
franks is the only one seeking a seat that has been held by a 
republican during the 1980s the incumbent gop rep john rowland 
is running for governor 
rowlands coattails are expected to help franks as is franks 
strong base in waterbury and an infusion of support from the 
national party 
voters in connecticuts 5th district a mixture of small towns 
suburbs and old industrial cities couldnt have a clearer choice 
franks is a fiscal conservative who preaches the virtues of the 
work ethic and the evils of a federal tax increase he favors a 
constitutional amendment to ban flagburning and supports a womans 
right to choose an abortion 
i believe in less government he said recently i believe 
that we dont have to tax and spend constantly to maintain our 
society 
moffett 46 went to congress as a naders raider with the 
watergate class of 1974 and served four terms before two 
unsuccessful bids for statewide office us senate in 1982 and 
governor in 1986 
moffett took a job as a television anchorman in hartford after 
his 1986 defeat when he moved into the 5th district to run for 
rowlands seat he immediately became the frontrunner despite 
being labeled a carpetbagger by opponents within and outside the 
party 
when i see mr moffett i think of the 70s said franks 
you think of jimmy carter you think of interest rates at 21 
percent you think of an unemployment rate of over 7 percent 
jay marlin moffetts campaign manager turns the tables by 
tying franks and his fiscal ideas to the reagan economic record 
if he wants to take credit for the reagan years he can take 
credit for a tax cut for the wealthy that hurt the middle class 
for the greatest deficits in history and for the savings and loan 
crisis marlin said 
that franks even won the gop nomination is considered a small 
miracle in waterbury he needed nine ballots at the partys 
convention last month to get its endorsement on the first six 
ballots he finished dead last 
but republican strategists say franks has a good chance of 
beating the betterknown moffett in a district where there are 
roughly 97000 registered democrats 83000 republicans and 107000 
unaffiliated voters 
from a purely political point of view hes from the right 
place waterbury said john mastropietro who is managing 
rowlands campaign for governor its extraordinarily difficult 
for a democrat to win the district without winning waterbury 
</TEXT>
