<TEXT>
no sooner did donald trump win some 
time to restructure his troubled financial empire than the clock 
began ticking for his next showdown with gambling regulators in 
october 
the casino control commission voted 50 to approve a bailout 
plan that pledges trumps three casinos as collateral for a 65 
million loan he received to make a bond payment on the trump castle 
hotel and casino 
but the commission decided to call trump in early for 
relicensing hearings on all three of his casinos because of 
questions surrounding his finances trump wasnt scheduled for the 
hearings until the spring but the commission wants to see him in 
october 
we must hold a financial stability hearing as soon as 
possible said acting commission chairwoman valerie armstrong 
the casino control act requires all casino enterprises to 
maintain financial stability integrity and responsibility 
we have approved the pledges without inquiring into whether 
the three trump properties continue to meet these standards and it 
is surely our obligation to conduct that inquiry as quickly as we 
can ms armstrong said 
the october hearing comes one month before trump must make a 47 
million bond payment due nov 15 on the trump taj mahal casino 
resort the state division of gaming enforcement which reluctantly 
endorsed trumps bailout said the developer will not make that 
payment under present conditions 
november is just around the corner and thats the immediate 
problem we face said thomas auriemma a deputy attorney general 
with the division if the money had not been advanced the whole 
trump organization would have faced in our opinion total 
collapse 
trumps attorneys also argued that his empire could have 
crumbled without the commissions approval 
ms armstrong said the commission shared the divisions lack of 
enthusiasm for the plan but would approve it as the best immediate 
hope for the solvency of trumps three casinos 
this is obviously a situation in which there are no good 
answers for mr trump or new jersey she said whether we 
approve or disapprove this restructuring our action will be 
fundamentally unsettling the risk of substantial economic 
disruption at the casinos will be less with the restructuring than 
it is without it 
trump wearing a blue tie blue suit and bluestriped shirt 
whispered occasionally during the 30minute hearing to his top 
executives but otherwise stared straight ahead unsmiling and with 
his lips pursed 
he repeatedly told a throng of reporters and camera crews 
afterward that the ruling left him happy he also restated his 
belief that his plight was not unusual because he feels the country 
is in a recession once the economy improves his assets will 
rebound he said 
this is a big hurdle and im happy trump told reporters 
maybe you can focus on someone else now 
