since its opening april 2 the taj has either fallen short or 
just reached the 13 million a day in gross gaming revenues that 
analysts say it needs to break even 
the taj mahal lost 144 million on gross revenue of 126 
million in its first three months ended june 30 according to 
figures released last week by the casino association of new jersey 
trump plaza hotel and casino had a profit of 876000 on gross 
revenues of 834 million while trump castle lost 81 million on 
gross revenues of 634 million 
in approving the bailout package the casino commission cited 
the benefits of an immediate infusion of 65 million deferred 
interest payments on outstanding loans and a requirement that 
banks holding at least twothirds of the loan find trump in default 
before action can be taken against him 
the approval also came with several reservations about the trump 
organization which has compiled more than 32 billion in debt on 
trumps casinos manhattan real estate trump shuttle airline and 
yacht the casinos bear responsibility for roughly 13 billion in 
debt 
ms armstrong said the agreement contains destabilizing features 
for the casinos including a link between the three properties that 
could prompt foreclosure at two trump gaming halls if financial 
problems arose at a third 
even more disturbing is the link the restructuring forges 
between the fate of the casinos and that of other trump assets 
ms armstrong said using a possible bankruptcy at the trump 
shuttle as one possible example 
trump faces 5405 million in overdue debts 2405 million of 
which he has personally guaranteed ms armstrong said he will 
face an additional 1695 million in debt by the end of april 
commissioners and the division both said trumps problems stand 
out as clear reasons why other casinos should avoid assuming huge 
amounts of debt 
