<TEXT>
each of the nations big three automakers 
on thursday are expected to give the united auto workers union 
comprehensive proposals for new threeyear contracts 
its likely that the uaw will not have much immediate reaction 
as they compare the documents from general motors corp ford motor 
co and chrysler corp 
the proposals will help the union decide probably on tuesday 
which company will be chosen as the unions target in this round of 
talks if tradition holds the union will use a contract reached 
with the target company as a pattern for contracts at the other two 
automakers most of the speculation about the target company 
centers on gm 
what happens here at these tables and at general motors and 
chrysler in the next few days will have a direct bearing as to who 
that target company will be uaw president owen bieber said 
wednesday during a visit to ford 
since all of them have indicated they would like to be the 
target they have a decision to make of whether they would be the 
quarterback or the substitute sitting on the bench 
automakers like to be the target since it gives them an 
opportunity to form a pattern agreement to their liking rather than 
one meeting the needs of a competitor 
chief ford negotiator jack hall declined wednesday to discuss 
the upcoming proposal saying only we think it is going to be 
responsive to the needs the union has expressed to us 
bieber has been making the rounds at each of the big three this 
week reminding negotiators that less than four weeks remain in the 
lives of the current agreements 
the three contracts cover more than 450000 active workers and 
expire sept 14 
bieber on wednesday visited ford where the atmosphere at the 
main bargaining table and in subcommittee meetings is less charged 
than at gm or chrysler 
as he did at gm on monday and was expected to do thursday at 
chrysler bieber said he was disappointed that ford had not offered 
a comprehensive proposal before now 
if i had my druthers i would wish that we would be further 
along than we are bieber said however i would also say that 
im convinced that there is ample time left to conclude an 
agreement provided that the pace picks up considerably now 
the uaw has been irritated at chrysler chief negotiator anthony 
st john talking about contract proposals with the media before 
describing them to the union st john said the company was 
interested in an employee ownership plan for the company forming a 
multiemployer healthcare trust to cut medical care costs and a 
new way to figure profit sharing 
uaw vice president stan marshall whos in charge of the 
chrysler department has said each of the proposals are as good as 
dead 
tensions rose at gm earlier this month when members of local 
659 at a flint parts plant walked off their jobs for six days in a 
local contract dispute 
that strike which affected production at seven assembly plants 
and a variety of component factories was unopposed by uaw national 
leaders it resulted in a contract guaranteeing the size of the 
work force at the plant for years to come 
the uaw has said job security is its top issue 
</TEXT>
