<TEXT>
pressure from competitors prompted several airlines wednesday to 
hold off fare increases even though the price of jet fuel keeps 
rising because of the persian gulf crisis 
american airlines continental airlines delta air lines and 
usair all said wednesday they would delay raising fares until aug 
30 
americans 53 percent fare increase originally was to have gone 
into effect thursday american based in fort worth texas cited 
competitive pressure for its delay the third since fare hikes were 
first announced aug 10 
if one airline decides to do something different they would 
gain a competitive market position and other airlines simply cannot 
allow that to happen said american spokeswoman mary oneill 
delta based in atlanta first planned to raise fares on aug 
15 and then this thursday but delayed the move to aug 30 in a 
competitive response to other airlines 
other major airlines have also responded to the middle east 
standoff by announcing a mixture of fare increases and discount 
rates designed to lure more passengers 
</TEXT>
