<TEXT>
the us commerce department has granted 
control data corp an export license to ship the most powerful 
computers ever sent to the soviet union from the west the company 
said tuesday 
control data will ship six cyber 960 mainframe computers worth a 
total of 32 million to the soviet union beginning in september 
the company said 
soviet president mikhail s gorbachev visited control data 
during his june stop in minnesota and viewed a demonstration of the 
cyber 960 computers gorbachev also spoke on the need for greater 
technological and commercial cooperation between the united states 
and the soviet union 
the computers were ordered by the soviet research and 
development institute of power engineering and will be used to 
analyze safety factors in the operation of civilian soviet nuclear 
power reactors 
the company applied for the export license last november and 
announced the soviet order on dec 12 1989 
control data worked with the us departments of commerce 
state defense and energy to put in place safeguards that the 
computers will be dedicated to safety analysis of civilian nuclear 
reactors the company said 
the soviet unions civilian nuclear power program is one of the 
largest in the world with about 50 plants in operation according 
to a control data statement last year half of the soviet unions 
nucleargenerated electricity was produced by plants designed by 
the institute that has ordered the control data computers the 
company said 
</TEXT>
