<TEXT>
atlanta journalconstitution has started offering 
to fax stock option tables to its readers 
the new service which began tuesday is part of the newspapers 
extra fax program the program launched in june permits readers 
who dial the extra fax number 222xfax to get more information 
over their fax machines 
its all free of charge 
the service had been used only for advertisements and allowed 
readers to dial the fax number put in the advertisers code and 
receive price lists coupons or sales announcements 
the new service provides figures for options and index options 
traded on the chicago american philadelphia and pacific exchanges 
the service is the newspapers first effort to expand its daily 
news report using facsimile said chris jennewein director of 
information services 
jennewein said the system was developed by mariettabased 
audiofax inc 
</TEXT>
